            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> please update the pr after reviewing https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#ai-assisted-work\r\n\r\ni reviewed the changes,\r\ntheres 14 line of changes to remove unused MAP_DECLS(U,T) which are: MAP_DECLS(int, int) , MAP_DECLS(uint64_t, ssize_t), MAP_DECLS(uint64_t, uint64_t) and also removing there defination of some functions from src/nvim/map.c because those are unused in the codebase.  we can check it out by  doing a regex search as following \r\n\r\n1st direct type usage:\r\nmap_(get|put|ref|del)\\(U,\\s*T\\) ( replacing U,T with the type we are intended to search). \r\n\r\n2nd indirect usage via macros ( these are used through another macros like for T=ptr_t)\r\n pmap_(get|put|del)\\(U\\)  \r\n \r\n about the removal of 2 static variables those are no longer needed bcz of the removal of correspoding U(data type). \r\n \r\n1. I double checked the change done by the ai\r\n2. I ran test locally to check if there is any problem\r\n3. there is no verbosity or extra files.\r\n4. theres no redundent code.\r\n\r\nREGEX SEARCH RESULT:\r\n```output\r\n/tmp/neovim fix/remove-unused-map-decls\r\n❯ rg 'map_(get|put|ref|del)\\(uint64_t,\\s*uint64_\\)' /tmp/neovim/src\r\n(No Output)\r\n\r\n/tmp/neovim fix/remove-unused-map-decls\r\n❯ rg 'map_(get|put|ref|del)\\(int,\\s*int\\)' /tmp/neovim/src\r\n\r\n/tmp/neovim fix/remove-unused-map-decls\r\n❯ rg 'map_(get|put|ref|del)\\(uint64_t,\\s*ssize_t\\)' /tmp/neovim/src\r\n```",
